In the present analysis, the problem of two-dimensional non-Newtonian second grade nanofluid with magnetic dipole effect and gyrotactic microorganism past a thin needle is performed. The effects of Arrhenius activation energy and binary chemical reaction are also detected with the analysis of entropy generation. The solution of the model is obtained by using the most powerful analytical method called the homotopy analysis method (HAM) using MATHEMATICA. Over the heat and mass transfer second-grade nanofluid flow, the effects of different physical parameters are determined. The following results are summarised asFigure 36
